race.comment: The first of the features and KING OF LIGHT (1) is clearly the one to beat. His late strength was a highlight of his Belgravia Stakes win and his improvement second-up and out to 1400m last campaign was very impressive. Can sit a touch closer this time around and keep his unbeaten streak alive. HEEZA PHOENIX (5) was very impressive through the winter at Belmont and stamped himself as a Guineas horse. His recent trial was very impressive over 1000m and he has plenty of untapped potential. Looks the main danger on what we've seen. STREAMLINED (11) is another with stacks up upside after a big win first-up over this trip at Belmont. He'll carry no weight for CJP and with improvement on the cards, he can make his presence felt. MARDUSA (3) was flying late in the Belgravia and wasn't beaten far in the finish. Rates highly on that effort and looks a key player. ROCK FEST (4) was only fair at the trials recently, but his form last campaign stacks right up. Keep safe.
